WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.386 --> 00:00:13.180
{\an8}- Structural collapse
at the water park--

2
00:00:13.263 --> 00:00:15.474
{\an8}two victims coming in
via helicopter.

3
00:00:15.557 --> 00:00:17.351
{\an8}ETA. five minutes.
- Time to rally the troops.

4
00:00:17.392 --> 00:00:18.644
{\an8}- I'll get environmental

5
00:00:18.727 --> 00:00:20.145
{\an8}to clear and prep
the trauma rooms.

6
00:00:20.229 --> 00:00:21.688
- Emma. restock
the crash carts.

7
00:00:21.772 --> 00:00:23.440
Makedah. take the latest
scripts to the drug cage.

8
00:00:23.524 --> 00:00:25.150
- Should be a fun one.
- "Fun one"? What's up?

9
00:00:25.234 --> 00:00:26.527
- Slide broke
at the water park--

10
00:00:26.568 --> 00:00:28.195
two victims.
five minutes to touchdown.

11
00:00:28.237 --> 00:00:29.863
No information
on extent of injuries.

12
00:00:29.905 --> 00:00:31.532
- I can jump in with--

13
00:00:31.573 --> 00:00:34.034
- Ogilvie. grab some goggles.
gloves. gown.

14
00:00:34.076 --> 00:00:35.285
Go up to the roof.

15
00:00:35.369 --> 00:00:36.703
First patient that lands.
bring 'em down.

16
00:00:36.787 --> 00:00:37.996
We got two choppers.

17
00:00:38.080 --> 00:00:39.915
You want to grab
some bodies and meet me?

18
00:00:39.998 --> 00:00:41.708
- What injuries
are we expecting?

19
00:00:41.792 --> 00:00:43.835
- Structural collapse.
Could be anything.

20
00:00:43.919 --> 00:00:46.380
- I can increase the morphine
drip to manage the pain.

21
00:00:46.421 --> 00:00:49.049
but that could also slow down
your breathing.

22
00:00:49.091 --> 00:00:50.926
You will likely feel
very drowsy.

23
00:00:51.009 --> 00:00:53.887
You may lose consciousness.

24
00:00:53.971 --> 00:00:57.099
And it could cause you
to stop breathing altogether.

25
00:00:59.434 --> 00:01:01.478
- [gasps. mouths words]

26
00:01:03.647 --> 00:01:06.066
[door closes]

27
00:01:06.108 --> 00:01:07.859
I'll be right back.

28
00:01:07.943 --> 00:01:10.946
[indistinct chatter]

29
00:01:15.284 --> 00:01:18.412
Hey. you okay?
- Yeah.

30
00:01:18.453 --> 00:01:19.746
Yeah. Sorry.

31
00:01:19.830 --> 00:01:23.208
- Look. it's hard seeing
your patients die.

32
00:01:23.250 --> 00:01:25.919
But as professionals. we have
to create emotional boundaries

33
00:01:26.003 --> 00:01:27.421
for ourselves.

34
00:01:27.462 --> 00:01:29.881
It's not about us.
It's about them.

35
00:01:31.967 --> 00:01:33.927
- She's so calm.
I just--

36
00:01:34.011 --> 00:01:36.013
- Yeah.

37
00:01:36.096 --> 00:01:39.891
She's had a long time
to prepare for this moment.

38
00:01:39.975 --> 00:01:42.102
What she's doing for her sons--

39
00:01:42.185 --> 00:01:44.938
managing this
with so much grace--

40
00:01:44.980 --> 00:01:46.607
it's a real gift of love.

41
00:01:46.690 --> 00:01:49.443
- I feel like an asshole.
[breathes deeply]

42
00:01:49.526 --> 00:01:51.612
All they want is more time
with their mother.

43
00:01:51.653 --> 00:01:53.322
All I want is less time
with mine.

44
00:01:53.405 --> 00:01:55.407
- Don't feel guilty.

45
00:01:55.490 --> 00:01:59.453
I mean. you can be grateful
and gracious from a distance.

46
00:01:59.494 --> 00:02:01.455
Just talk to her.
Tell her what you want.

47
00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:04.583
She'll understand.

48
00:02:04.666 --> 00:02:07.628
- I just--I doubt that.

49
00:02:07.669 --> 00:02:10.881
- Give her a chance. you know?
She may surprise you.

50
00:02:13.258 --> 00:02:14.676
- Hey.

51
00:02:14.760 --> 00:02:16.637
Two birds headed our way.
Need a hand?

52
00:02:16.720 --> 00:02:18.263
- That's the rumor.

53
00:02:18.347 --> 00:02:21.266
Santos. trauma incoming.
Grab a gown.

54
00:02:21.350 --> 00:02:23.644
You can assist Dr. Langdon.

55
00:02:23.685 --> 00:02:25.646
[elevator bell dings]

56
00:02:25.687 --> 00:02:27.105
- Fuck me.

57
00:02:27.189 --> 00:02:29.900
- Jesus. I got blood tubes
growing moss over here.

58
00:02:29.983 --> 00:02:31.985
Ticktock. people.

59
00:02:32.027 --> 00:02:34.279
Hey. Olive. do me a solid--
run these to the lab.

60
00:02:34.363 --> 00:02:35.447
- No problem.

61
00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:37.324
- Uh. I got more lab results.

62
00:02:37.407 --> 00:02:39.493
- Start putting them
on the patient clipboards.

63
00:02:39.534 --> 00:02:41.662
- PTMC Emergency.
Go ahead. Medic Command.

64
00:02:41.745 --> 00:02:43.330
- Do cyber attacks
happen often?

65
00:02:43.413 --> 00:02:45.540
- More than you realize.
- I blame the Russkies.

66
00:02:45.624 --> 00:02:48.669
- Dr. Mohan. it's your mother?

67
00:02:48.710 --> 00:02:50.337
She sounds pretty upset.

68
00:02:50.420 --> 00:02:53.298
Says she really needs
to talk to you.

69
00:02:53.382 --> 00:02:54.508
- You're shitting me.

70
00:02:54.549 --> 00:02:56.593
Um. tell her I'm not available.

71
00:02:59.513 --> 00:03:02.557
[helicopter whirring loudly]

72
00:03:06.186 --> 00:03:08.313
- How's your shift going?

73
00:03:08.397 --> 00:03:10.982
- It's been a lot already.

74
00:03:11.024 --> 00:03:14.194
You know. I worked in an ER
before. up in Vermont.

75
00:03:14.236 --> 00:03:17.906
and we had MVAs and ODs. MIs.

76
00:03:17.989 --> 00:03:19.700
But this place...

77
00:03:19.783 --> 00:03:22.077
this place is relentless.

78
00:03:22.160 --> 00:03:25.706
- Holiday weekend.
We're not normally offline.

79
00:03:25.789 --> 00:03:28.709
- I think we have a very
different idea of normal.

80
00:03:28.750 --> 00:03:30.168
- It's not for everyone.

81
00:03:30.252 --> 00:03:32.629
- I'm not sure it's healthy
for anybody.

82
00:03:32.713 --> 00:03:34.339
- Here's her leg.

83
00:03:34.423 --> 00:03:36.174
- Jesus.

84
00:03:42.764 --> 00:03:44.141
- I need more runners.

85
00:03:44.224 --> 00:03:45.976
- Oh. you could shut down
the gift shop.

86
00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:48.103
They always have a couple
of volunteers there.

87
00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:50.105
- Most of those volunteers
use walkers.

88
00:03:50.188 --> 00:03:51.732
- [chuckles]
Beggars can't be choosers.

89
00:03:51.815 --> 00:03:53.191
- Go get 'em.

90
00:03:53.275 --> 00:03:55.110
- Okay. I'm gonna grab
a smoke first.

91
00:03:55.193 --> 00:03:57.404
- No time. Nicotine gum--
take the edge off.

92
00:03:57.446 --> 00:03:59.740
You two. head to triage to help
out the front of the house.

93
00:03:59.823 --> 00:04:01.116
They're running out of space.

94
00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:02.909
and there's a line
out the door.

95
00:04:02.993 --> 00:04:05.871
- Okay. let's go.
- Hang on. Mohan.

96
00:04:05.954 --> 00:04:08.165
Sign this.

97
00:04:10.459 --> 00:04:12.085
- Nicotine patch.
21 milligrams.

98
00:04:12.127 --> 00:04:13.587
Who's it for?

99
00:04:13.628 --> 00:04:15.005
- Monica.
This nicotine gum's shit.

100
00:04:15.088 --> 00:04:16.506
She'll never survive the shift.

101
00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:18.884
and I need her so I don't lose
my goddamn mind.

102
00:04:20.844 --> 00:04:22.095
Thanks.

103
00:04:22.137 --> 00:04:23.805
- Is Dr. Abbot still around?

104
00:04:23.889 --> 00:04:25.307
- He went to get some sleep

105
00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:27.142
before his night shift
starts in a couple hours.

106
00:04:27.225 --> 00:04:29.394
- Shit. Okay. I should have
planned this better.

107
00:04:29.436 --> 00:04:32.147
I was hoping he'd write me
a letter of rec for an elective

108
00:04:32.230 --> 00:04:34.566
so I could have a shot
at a fellowship next year.

109
00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:36.276
- Which one?

110
00:04:36.359 --> 00:04:38.195
- Whichever will take me.

111
00:04:38.278 --> 00:04:40.405
- Didn't the electives fill up
a while ago?

112
00:04:40.489 --> 00:04:41.948
- Don't remind me.

113
00:04:42.032 --> 00:04:43.784
I'm gonna throw myself
at the mercy of the court.

114
00:04:43.867 --> 00:04:45.202
beg for them to take me anyway.

115
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:47.412
Just kill me now.
It'll be less painful.

116
00:04:47.496 --> 00:04:49.748
- Dana. I can't read
this handwriting.

117
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:51.416
- It says...

118
00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:54.085
1.000 milligrams
acetaminophen orally.

119
00:04:54.169 --> 00:04:56.421
4 milligrams ondansetron
under the tongue.

120
00:04:56.505 --> 00:04:58.632
and trial of clear fluids.

121
00:04:58.673 --> 00:05:00.175
- Seriously?
It says all that?

122
00:05:00.258 --> 00:05:02.177
- If it's not in a text
with emojis.

123
00:05:02.260 --> 00:05:03.929
you kids can't read for shit.

124
00:05:06.515 --> 00:05:07.974
- What do we have?

125
00:05:08.058 --> 00:05:10.060
- A fall from 10 feet
onto a metal fence.

126
00:05:10.143 --> 00:05:11.937
Right below the knee.
Good vitals.

127
00:05:12.020 --> 00:05:13.647
- Oh. it hurts.
Oh. my God.

128
00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:15.982
- What's she had so far?
- 50 of fent. repeated 25.

129
00:05:16.066 --> 00:05:17.818
No meds. no allergies.

130
00:05:17.859 --> 00:05:19.778
- Where should I put this?
- Just hang on to it for now.

131
00:05:19.861 --> 00:05:23.615
- On my count.
One. two. three.

132
00:05:23.698 --> 00:05:25.325
[person groans in pain]

133
00:05:25.408 --> 00:05:28.537
- Okay. Whitaker. E-FAST.
Donnie. primary survey. please.

134
00:05:28.620 --> 00:05:31.331
- Pupils equal and reactive.

135
00:05:31.414 --> 00:05:33.834
What's your name?
- My leg hurts really bad.

136
00:05:33.917 --> 00:05:35.669
Did I break it?

137
00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:37.671
- Um. I-I wouldn't say
that it's broken exactly.

138
00:05:37.754 --> 00:05:39.464
- We're gonna get an X-ray
to determine that.

139
00:05:39.506 --> 00:05:41.466
Put that on the gurney.
line it up for X-ray.

140
00:05:41.550 --> 00:05:43.009
keep your fucking mouth shut.

141
00:05:43.093 --> 00:05:44.761
- Good lung sliding
right and left.

142
00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:47.472
- Airway patent.
breath sounds bilaterally.

143
00:05:47.556 --> 00:05:49.933
- Please. it hurts.
- BP 100 over 60.

144
00:05:50.016 --> 00:05:52.978
Pulse 118. pulse ox 98%.

145
00:05:53.019 --> 00:05:56.231
- Does your belly hurt?
- No. asshole! It's my leg!

146
00:05:56.314 --> 00:05:58.024
- Okay. she's
really moving here.

147
00:05:58.066 --> 00:05:59.359
- 100 of ketamine?

148
00:05:59.442 --> 00:06:02.028
- Yeah. we can't evaluate
like this.

149
00:06:02.112 --> 00:06:03.989
- Hey. Ogilvie?

150
00:06:04.030 --> 00:06:06.157
Deep breaths. yeah?
- Yeah. okay.

151
00:06:06.241 --> 00:06:07.659
- Whitaker. what's next?

152
00:06:07.742 --> 00:06:10.203
- Uh. once she's sedated.
finish the E-FAST.

153
00:06:10.287 --> 00:06:12.163
plain X-ray. check her back.
straight to CT.

154
00:06:12.247 --> 00:06:14.040
- What if the ketamine
wears off?

155
00:06:14.124 --> 00:06:15.500
- Right. Uh. we should do

156
00:06:15.584 --> 00:06:18.128
a popliteal nerve block
before the CT.

157
00:06:18.211 --> 00:06:20.046
anesthetize from the knee down.

158
00:06:20.088 --> 00:06:21.923
- Two view tib-fib.
- Pushing ketamine now.

159
00:06:22.007 --> 00:06:23.258
- What's the bullet?

160
00:06:23.341 --> 00:06:25.260
- 42-year-old male
with 20-foot fall.

161
00:06:25.343 --> 00:06:27.429
Blunt chest trauma
with hand injury.

162
00:06:27.512 --> 00:06:29.431
- Where's my son?
Where's my son?

163
00:06:29.514 --> 00:06:31.850
- He's tachy to 108.
sats 98 on 2 liters.

164
00:06:31.933 --> 00:06:33.518
BP 122 over 84.

165
00:06:33.602 --> 00:06:35.270
- We'll pan scan
due to mechanism.

166
00:06:35.353 --> 00:06:37.230
You?
- Tib-fib amputation.

167
00:06:37.314 --> 00:06:39.482
Hoping ortho can. uh. give us
a little hope for replantation.

168
00:06:39.566 --> 00:06:42.152
- Derek. where are you hurting?
- Chest and my finger.

169
00:06:42.235 --> 00:06:43.403
Did they find my son?

170
00:06:43.486 --> 00:06:45.530
- Did you hit your head?
- Don't think so.

171
00:06:45.614 --> 00:06:46.823
I need to find my son!

172
00:06:46.907 --> 00:06:48.074
- We'll find him for you.

173
00:06:48.158 --> 00:06:50.368
but we need to take care
of you first.

174
00:06:50.452 --> 00:06:52.412
- Pericardium's clear.
No fluid in Morrison's.

175
00:06:52.495 --> 00:06:54.539
- Move both arms.
wiggle your feet.

176
00:06:54.623 --> 00:06:56.917
Good. Any pain in your neck?
- No.

177
00:06:57.000 --> 00:06:59.044
- Spleen looks good.
- Start with his chest.

178
00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:00.295
That's where he hurts.

179
00:07:00.378 --> 00:07:02.923
No hemotympanum.
- Normal sliding.

180
00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:05.592
- Best to start with the side
he's complaining about first.

181
00:07:05.675 --> 00:07:08.470
- Uh. I don't see
much sliding there.

182
00:07:08.553 --> 00:07:10.555
- His name is Zack.
He's seven.

183
00:07:10.639 --> 00:07:12.766
- Pneumothorax?
- Set up for a chest tube.

184
00:07:12.807 --> 00:07:15.393
- Not yet.
Uh. let's go posterolateral.

185
00:07:15.477 --> 00:07:17.062
Look for fluid first.

186
00:07:17.145 --> 00:07:19.439
- Traumatic pneumothorax.
We should prep the chest.

187
00:07:19.481 --> 00:07:21.900
- Not necessarily.
He's hemodynamically stable.

188
00:07:21.983 --> 00:07:23.693
- Okay.

189
00:07:23.777 --> 00:07:25.278
Does that look like
some fluid there?

190
00:07:25.362 --> 00:07:26.821
- Hard to say for sure.

191
00:07:26.905 --> 00:07:28.907
- Okay. he's tachycardic
hemopneumothorax.

192
00:07:28.990 --> 00:07:30.241
He needs a chest tube.

193
00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:32.243
- BP and sats are fine.
We can wait for CT.

194
00:07:32.327 --> 00:07:33.954
If it's small.
it'll resolve on its own.

195
00:07:34.037 --> 00:07:35.956
We observe and reimage.
- I agree. He's stable for now.

196
00:07:36.039 --> 00:07:37.958
Let's wait for the scan.
Dr. Santos.

197
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:39.960
- Okay. let's order...
- Okay.

198
00:07:40.043 --> 00:07:43.296
- A CT chest. abdomen.
pelvis. and X-ray left hand.

199
00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:46.216
- Whoa. major degloving.
- Focus on the primary.

200
00:07:46.299 --> 00:07:49.135
- Dr. Langdon's correct.
We need to logroll him.

201
00:07:49.219 --> 00:07:50.804
- [shouting in pain]
- Oh. okay.

202
00:07:50.845 --> 00:07:52.806
How about another four
of morphine?

203
00:07:52.889 --> 00:07:54.808
- Put it in.
Hang in there. Derek.

204
00:07:54.849 --> 00:07:57.143
- We got you.
- [mouths words]

205
00:07:57.185 --> 00:07:59.604
[cell phone vibrating]
- Fuck off already.

206
00:07:59.688 --> 00:08:02.148
- Boyfriend?
- Wish. My mom.

207
00:08:02.232 --> 00:08:04.150
Every time I get
a second of service.

208
00:08:04.234 --> 00:08:05.610
another dozen texts come in.
- Hey!

209
00:08:05.694 --> 00:08:07.487
How much longer
do I have to wait?

210
00:08:07.529 --> 00:08:08.822
I got a broken leg here.

211
00:08:08.863 --> 00:08:10.490
- Someone will be
with you shortly. sir.

212
00:08:10.573 --> 00:08:12.158
- Am I allowed
to use the bathroom?

213
00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:13.994
I really have to go.
- I don't know. ma'am.

214
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:15.161
I am not your doctor.

215
00:08:15.245 --> 00:08:16.830
- It says right there
"doctor."

216
00:08:16.871 --> 00:08:18.331
- Yes. but I'm not <i>your</i> doctor.

217
00:08:18.415 --> 00:08:20.000
But if you go
back to your room.

218
00:08:20.083 --> 00:08:22.460
a nurse will come find you.
- I wasn't in a room.

219
00:08:22.502 --> 00:08:25.422
- I'm sorry. Um. are either
of you treating my mother?

220
00:08:25.505 --> 00:08:27.841
- Nope!

221
00:08:27.924 --> 00:08:30.969
[breathing heavily]

222
00:08:33.471 --> 00:08:35.849
- Take a seat.
It's gonna be a while.

223
00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:38.852
[indistinct chatter]

224
00:08:38.893 --> 00:08:41.229
Helen Torres. come on down.

225
00:08:42.814 --> 00:08:44.858
Helen Torres?

226
00:08:44.899 --> 00:08:46.985
- [speaking Spanish]

227
00:08:48.903 --> 00:08:52.532
- [speaking Spanish]
- [speaking Spanish]

228
00:08:56.745 --> 00:09:00.040
[door buzzes]

229
00:09:00.123 --> 00:09:01.207
- Thank you.

230
00:09:01.291 --> 00:09:03.585
Ay.
[winces]

231
00:09:06.296 --> 00:09:08.173
- I'm Dr. Mohan.
This is Student Doctor Kwon.

232
00:09:08.256 --> 00:09:09.716
- Helen.

233
00:09:09.799 --> 00:09:12.010
- How long has your leg been
swollen. Helen?

234
00:09:12.093 --> 00:09:14.846
- Uh. it's been getting worse
over the past week.

235
00:09:14.929 --> 00:09:16.681
- Dr. Mohan. your mom
called again.

236
00:09:16.765 --> 00:09:18.224
She said you need
to call her back.

237
00:09:18.308 --> 00:09:19.225
- Not now!

238
00:09:19.309 --> 00:09:21.144
I'm with a patient.

239
00:09:23.271 --> 00:09:24.814
Sorry about that.

240
00:09:24.898 --> 00:09:27.692
Um. did you--did you fall
or hit your leg?

241
00:09:27.776 --> 00:09:29.527
- No.

242
00:09:29.611 --> 00:09:32.697
Have--have you ever had
a blood clot before?

243
00:09:32.781 --> 00:09:34.699
- No.
- [inhales deeply]

244
00:09:34.783 --> 00:09:36.910
[grunts softly]

245
00:09:36.951 --> 00:09:39.621
- Are you all right?
- Excuse me?

246
00:09:39.704 --> 00:09:43.083
- Do you need to sit down?
- Oh. no. I'm--I'm fine.

247
00:09:43.124 --> 00:09:44.709
- You don't look too good.

248
