Uh. uh. stop.

497
00:20:38.237 --> 00:20:40.740
Irrigate the ring shavings
off first.

498
00:20:40.823 --> 00:20:43.242
[telephone rings]
- What did I miss?

499
00:20:43.325 --> 00:20:45.244
- Finishing irrigation.

500
00:20:45.327 --> 00:20:46.579
Okay.

501
00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:48.205
Doesn't look like
you lost any skin.

502
00:20:48.247 --> 00:20:50.541
- It's a little dusky.
Might not be viable.

503
00:20:50.624 --> 00:20:52.376
- There's intact skin
on the dorsum.

504
00:20:52.460 --> 00:20:54.754
- More irrigation. then tack
it down with one suture.

505
00:20:54.795 --> 00:20:56.255
- Okay. thanks.

506
00:20:56.297 --> 00:20:58.883
Radiologist reports
a 25% pneumothorax.

507
00:20:58.966 --> 00:21:00.634
- Is that bad?

508
00:21:00.718 --> 00:21:03.053
- That is a partially collapsed
lung that needs treatment.

509
00:21:03.137 --> 00:21:05.639
- I can put in a chest tube.
- He doesn't need a chest tube.

510
00:21:05.723 --> 00:21:07.767
- Okay. what do you want--
a pigtail catheter?

511
00:21:07.850 --> 00:21:10.144
- I was thinking a ThoraVent.

512
00:21:10.227 --> 00:21:11.645
- What? Why?

513
00:21:11.729 --> 00:21:13.939
- It's not a bad idea.
No need for wall suction.

514
00:21:14.023 --> 00:21:15.441
- If Hand can operate today.

515
00:21:15.524 --> 00:21:17.401
he can go home tomorrow
with the ThoraVent.

516
00:21:17.485 --> 00:21:19.612
- You can learn a lot
from your senior residents.

517
00:21:19.653 --> 00:21:21.655
- I'm happy
to teach Dr. Santos.

518
00:21:21.739 --> 00:21:23.908
- Thank you. Dr. Langdon.

519
00:21:27.620 --> 00:21:30.790
- Janelle. I need you to take
the samples to the lab

520
00:21:30.831 --> 00:21:32.917
and come back with any results
that are ready.

521
00:21:32.958 --> 00:21:35.544
Geoffrey. head to CT to see
if any new results are printed

522
00:21:35.628 --> 00:21:37.129
and bring those back.

523
00:21:37.171 --> 00:21:39.757
Pam. check in
with whoever's running the PDS

524
00:21:39.840 --> 00:21:41.801
to see if any orders
need to go to the pharmacy

525
00:21:41.884 --> 00:21:44.136
and bring back any meds
that are ready for pickup.

526
00:21:44.178 --> 00:21:46.597
Rinse and repeat
every 15 minutes.

527
00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:48.599
- Double-tie those shoelaces
and hydrate.

528
00:21:48.682 --> 00:21:51.310
It's not a sprint.
It's a marathon.

529
00:21:51.352 --> 00:21:53.646
- Fly. my pretties.

530
00:21:53.687 --> 00:21:56.816
Okay. any word on finding
our water slide dad's kid?

531
00:21:56.899 --> 00:22:00.319
- Not yet. Called the wife.
went straight to voicemail.

532
00:22:00.361 --> 00:22:02.655
Police dispatch said that there
were a couple of fatalities

533
00:22:02.696 --> 00:22:05.783
on site--one adult. one kid.
- Sweet Jesus.

534
00:22:05.866 --> 00:22:07.535
Who the fuck did this?

535
00:22:07.618 --> 00:22:09.662
No sign-off on orders
for labs or X-rays.

536
00:22:09.703 --> 00:22:11.455
and it's in the wrong
freaking rack?

537
00:22:11.497 --> 00:22:13.707
You guys trying to kill me
and the patient?

538
00:22:13.791 --> 00:22:15.668
- Uh. I'll take care of it.
- Thanks.

539
00:22:15.709 --> 00:22:18.838
- Dana. this gum is abso--
- Shit. I know.

540
00:22:18.921 --> 00:22:20.840
- Pharmacy said you needed this
right away.

541
00:22:20.923 --> 00:22:23.384
- Just in time. Slap one on
and give it an hour to kick in.

542
00:22:23.467 --> 00:22:25.636
You're welcome.

543
00:22:25.719 --> 00:22:28.514
What?
- The prescription is for you.

544
00:22:28.556 --> 00:22:31.016
- My insurance will cover it.
Hers won't.

545
00:22:31.100 --> 00:22:33.185
- Isn't that insurance fraud?

546
00:22:33.269 --> 00:22:35.646
- Throw me in jail.
I could use a vacation.

547
00:22:35.729 --> 00:22:37.147
- [chuckles]

548
00:22:37.231 --> 00:22:39.024
- [clears throat]

549
00:22:39.108 --> 00:22:40.776
- Mom.

550
00:22:44.738 --> 00:22:47.283
I'm--I'm really glad
to see you. Mom. I--

551
00:22:47.366 --> 00:22:49.785
- Garcia told me about the
sigmoid volvulus you missed.

552
00:22:49.869 --> 00:22:52.288
- It was an oversight.
- That could have killed her.

553
00:22:52.371 --> 00:22:53.873
- Without electronic records.

554
00:22:53.914 --> 00:22:55.791
it's been kind of a challenge
to figure out--

555
00:22:55.875 --> 00:22:57.376
- Chaos is the status quo
in the ED.

556
00:22:57.418 --> 00:22:59.253
even when the computers
are working properly.

557
00:22:59.336 --> 00:23:01.255
You have to be hypervigilant
and double-check everything.

558
00:23:01.338 --> 00:23:03.757
- I can handle it. Um. I--
- Why would you want to?

559
00:23:03.841 --> 00:23:05.718
Down here your learning
street-level medicine.

560
00:23:05.759 --> 00:23:07.386
all seat of your pants.

561
00:23:07.469 --> 00:23:08.888
Oh. well. I made a mistake.

562
00:23:08.971 --> 00:23:10.890
but the more talented
practitioners upstairs

563
00:23:10.973 --> 00:23:12.725
will fix it.

564
00:23:12.766 --> 00:23:16.520
[sighs]
You are better than this.

565
00:23:16.604 --> 00:23:20.024
- [sighing]
I love you. too.

566
00:23:24.153 --> 00:23:27.072
- Well. that is one way
to do a debrief.

567
00:23:27.156 --> 00:23:28.407
- You should talk to her.

568
00:23:28.449 --> 00:23:30.868
- Which one?
- Honestly. both of them.

569
00:23:30.951 --> 00:23:32.912
- Can you call in
some extra doctors?

570
00:23:32.953 --> 00:23:35.831
- Sure. Everyone's dying
to work on the Fourth of July.

571
00:23:35.915 --> 00:23:37.416
Why?
- Dr. Mohan went down.

572
00:23:37.499 --> 00:23:40.336
- Yeah.
I saw your pep talk.

573
00:23:40.419 --> 00:23:43.339
- She's taking a little break
until her labs are back.

574
00:23:43.422 --> 00:23:44.757
She's going to be fine.

575
00:23:44.798 --> 00:23:47.384
but I'm not sure her head
is in the game.

576
00:23:47.468 --> 00:23:49.053
- I'm on it. Cap.

577
00:23:49.094 --> 00:23:50.930
- Small stab incision
with the 11 blade.

578
00:23:51.013 --> 00:23:53.933
midclavicular line.
second intercostal space.

579
00:23:54.016 --> 00:23:57.227
- Sh--she's gonna stab me?
- It's just a medical term.

580
00:23:57.311 --> 00:23:59.355
- Stay superior to the rib.

581
00:23:59.438 --> 00:24:03.317
[monitor beeping]

582
00:24:03.400 --> 00:24:05.277
- Is there a problem?

583
00:24:05.319 --> 00:24:07.655
- Nope. everything's
going well.

584
00:24:07.738 --> 00:24:09.782
- Place the trocar.

585
00:24:09.823 --> 00:24:12.451
Hold back
the. uh. adhesive wings

586
00:24:12.534 --> 00:24:15.829
and advance until you see
the red diaphragm move.

587
00:24:15.913 --> 00:24:18.666
That means you're
in the pleural space.

588
00:24:18.749 --> 00:24:21.168
Now remove the trocar.

589
00:24:24.588 --> 00:24:27.007
- Perfect.
- Okay.

590
00:24:27.091 --> 00:24:29.510
Now we can either. uh. hook up
to wall suction.

591
00:24:29.593 --> 00:24:31.637
or we can use
this one-way valve

592
00:24:31.679 --> 00:24:33.597
to repeatedly aspirate
with a syringe.

593
00:24:33.681 --> 00:24:35.975
- Well. with all your vast
experience. Dr. Langdon.

594
00:24:36.058 --> 00:24:38.102
you should probably decide.

595
00:24:39.853 --> 00:24:42.606
- We can avoid wall suction
if I pump manually.

596
00:24:42.690 --> 00:24:44.274
- Have at it. Doc.
- Enough.

597
00:24:44.316 --> 00:24:46.610
Apparently. decency and decorum
need to be reintroduced

598
00:24:46.694 --> 00:24:48.654
to our R2 curriculum.

599
00:24:48.696 --> 00:24:50.447
- Nice work. Dr. Langdon.

600
00:24:50.531 --> 00:24:53.993
I'll go check on an OR
for Mr. Foster.

601
00:24:54.076 --> 00:24:57.121
[door opens. closes]

602
00:24:57.204 --> 00:24:58.622
- Hey.

603
00:24:58.706 --> 00:25:01.166
I'm gonna need you
to pick up the pace.

604
00:25:01.250 --> 00:25:02.626
- Can I get a sec?

605
00:25:02.710 --> 00:25:04.837
Dr. Mohan just
almost died on me.

606
00:25:04.878 --> 00:25:06.839
- Not even close.
She's tougher than she looks.

607
00:25:06.880 --> 00:25:08.674
Propane hero in North 4.

608
00:25:08.757 --> 00:25:10.300
- Hey. any word from surgery

609
00:25:10.342 --> 00:25:12.845
on how are big patient Howard's
perforated diverticulitis

610
00:25:12.886 --> 00:25:14.388
is doing?
- Still in the OR.

611
00:25:14.471 --> 00:25:16.015
- What about our drunk
firework kid?

612
00:25:16.098 --> 00:25:18.017
- Waiting his turn
in the surgical conga line.

613
00:25:18.100 --> 00:25:20.185
- Shoo.
What about Social Services?

614
00:25:20.269 --> 00:25:22.396
Have they found
a temporary foster home

615
00:25:22.479 --> 00:25:24.815
for our baby Jane Doe?
- Still working on it.

616
00:25:24.898 --> 00:25:26.650
- Kid's gonna be
old enough to drive

617
00:25:26.734 --> 00:25:28.402
by the time
she gets out of here.

618
00:25:28.485 --> 00:25:29.862
- You joke...

619
00:25:29.903 --> 00:25:32.031
Oh. for fuck's sake!

620
00:25:32.114 --> 00:25:35.492
Go. quickly.
before I change my mind.

621
00:25:35.576 --> 00:25:38.203
- Hey. did the county pick up
Louie's body yet?

622
00:25:38.287 --> 00:25:39.872
- No. He's still
in the viewing room.

623
00:25:39.913 --> 00:25:41.540
- Jesus.
He's just laying in there?

624
00:25:41.582 --> 00:25:43.542
- Yeah. Another couple minutes.
I'm gonna wheel him

625
00:25:43.625 --> 00:25:45.878
down to the morgue myself.

626
00:25:45.919 --> 00:25:47.546
- What's the bullet?

627
00:25:47.629 --> 00:25:49.465
- Eight-year-old boy. part
of the water park accident.

628
00:25:49.548 --> 00:25:51.300
Thrown off the water slide.
- How far did he fall?

629
00:25:51.383 --> 00:25:53.218
- Maybe 6 or 7 feet.
landed in a tree.

630
00:25:53.302 --> 00:25:55.220
Had to wait for a ladder truck
to get him down.

631
00:25:55.262 --> 00:25:57.222
- Major neck trauma--must've
taken all the impact there.

632
00:25:57.306 --> 00:25:59.058
- Couldn't tube him.
hard to bag.

633
00:25:59.141 --> 00:26:01.477
Sats in the 80s.
BP 85 over 60.

634
00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:04.146
Pulse 50.

635
00:26:04.229 --> 00:26:08.108
- Okay. one. two. and three.

636
00:26:08.192 --> 00:26:10.778
- Possible laryngeal fracture.
- Hypoxic bradycardic.

637
00:26:10.861 --> 00:26:12.905
- Kid needs an airway
before he arrests.

638
00:26:12.988 --> 00:26:15.365
- Broselow tape. pedes cart.
set up suction.

639
00:26:15.449 --> 00:26:18.243
- Oh. my God.
Is that Zack?

640
00:26:18.285 --> 00:26:20.913
- Hey.
Hey. kid. can you look at me?

641
00:26:20.954 --> 00:26:24.291
No response. no purposeful
movement to pain.

642
00:26:24.374 --> 00:26:26.126
- Oh. my God.

643
00:26:26.210 --> 00:26:28.462
- Is this your kid?
- No.

644
00:26:28.545 --> 00:26:29.922
- Sir. go back
to your room now.

645
00:26:29.963 --> 00:26:31.423
- Broselow says 25 kilograms.
- Jesse?

646
00:26:31.507 --> 00:26:33.258
- 5 1/2 ET tube.
- Okay.

647
00:26:33.342 --> 00:26:36.095
Uh. 30 of rock. 50 ketamine.

648
00:26:36.136 --> 00:26:37.596
- You're gonna paralyze?
- Yep.

649
00:26:37.679 --> 00:26:38.931
- If we can't intubate.
we crike?

650
00:26:38.972 --> 00:26:40.516
- He's too young for a crike.

651
00:26:40.599 --> 00:26:42.601
- Needle crike?
- Can't ventilate through that.

652
00:26:42.643 --> 00:26:43.894
- Sats down to 78.

653
00:26:43.977 --> 00:26:45.729
- 11 blade. Kelly.
and a pedes bougie.

654
00:26:45.813 --> 00:26:47.606
One quick look.
and then we cut.

655
00:26:47.648 --> 00:26:49.608
- I can't tell
if there's lung sliding.

656
00:26:49.650 --> 00:26:51.693
No movement. no air entry.
- Way too edematous.

657
00:26:51.777 --> 00:26:53.028
I can't see the cords.

658
00:26:53.112 --> 00:26:56.281
- Better with cricoid pressure?
- Nothing. Fuck.

659
00:26:56.365 --> 00:26:58.117
- Okay. Towel roll between
the shoulder blades. please.

660
00:26:58.200 --> 00:27:00.119
- Heart rate down to 49.
Headed to cardiac arrest.

661
00:27:00.202 --> 00:27:01.620
Trake's going to take
20 minutes.

662
00:27:01.662 --> 00:27:03.413
This kid's not gonna
last 60 seconds.

663
00:27:03.497 --> 00:27:05.040
- That's why we're
doing a slash trake.

664
00:27:05.124 --> 00:27:06.291
- Don't know it.
- Me neither.

665
00:27:06.375 --> 00:27:08.127
- Boss?
- Show me what you got.

666
00:27:08.210 --> 00:27:11.755
[monitor beeping rapidly]

667
00:27:16.802 --> 00:27:20.639
- Pull up the trachea between
your thumb and middle finger.

668
00:27:20.681 --> 00:27:23.684
Vertical incision
right over the trachea.

669
00:27:23.767 --> 00:27:26.687
Vertical. not horizontal.
or you transect the trachea

670
00:27:26.770 --> 00:27:29.481
and cut the jugular veins.

671
00:27:29.523 --> 00:27:30.816
- That's a lot of blood.

672
00:27:30.899 --> 00:27:33.152
- Now it's a tactile procedure.

673
00:27:33.235 --> 00:27:36.530
2-centimeter incision
through the tracheal rings.

674
00:27:36.613 --> 00:27:39.533
Finger in the trachea.

675
00:27:39.616 --> 00:27:41.702
Bougie into the airway.

676
00:27:43.412 --> 00:27:45.330
Thoughts on what's next.
Dr. Whitaker?

677
00:27:45.414 --> 00:27:48.250
- Insert the ET tube
into the trachea.

678
00:27:48.333 --> 00:27:50.836
- Suction.
Lots of blood in the airway.

679
00:27:50.878 --> 00:27:53.881
[device slurping]

680
00:27:57.092 --> 00:27:59.303
Okay. bag him.

681
00:27:59.386 --> 00:28:01.805
Check the CO2.

682
00:28:01.889 --> 00:28:03.807
- Sats coming up. in the 80s.

683
00:28:03.849 --> 00:28:06.810
- Bilateral breath sounds.
End tidal CO2 is 70.

684
00:28:06.894 --> 00:28:08.604
That's crazy high.
- It'll come down.

685
00:28:08.687 --> 00:28:10.772
Tie down the tube.
control all the bleeders.

686
00:28:10.856 --> 00:28:13.192
Spray an amp of epi
on a stack of 4-by-4s.

687
00:28:13.275 --> 00:28:15.986
- Okay.
Sats are up to the 90s.

688
00:28:16.069 --> 00:28:18.363
Good. CO2's in the 50s.
Good heart rate.

689
00:28:18.447 --> 00:28:19.907
- You forgot the last step.

690
00:28:19.990 --> 00:28:21.867
Change your underwear.
- [chuckles]

691
00:28:21.909 --> 00:28:24.536
- How many of these you done?
- Uh. first one.

692
00:28:24.578 --> 00:28:25.829
- You serious?

693
00:28:25.913 --> 00:28:27.581
How about you?
- None.

694
00:28:27.664 --> 00:28:30.209
- I practiced in the Sim Lab
when I was at Stanford.

695
00:28:30.292 --> 00:28:31.835
- What'd I miss?
- All the fun.

696
00:28:31.919 --> 00:28:33.545
- Slash trake.
- Seriously?

697
00:28:33.629 --> 00:28:35.005
- Uh. fractured larynx.

698
00:28:35.088 --> 00:28:36.757
Couldn't oxygenate.
couldn't ventilate.

699
00:28:36.840 --> 00:28:38.842
- You use a meat cleaver
on this kid?

700
00:28:38.926 --> 00:28:41.220
- ENT can revise
the trake in the OR.

701
00:28:41.261 --> 00:28:43.847
- They'll be thrilled
to clean up your mess.

702
00:28:43.931 --> 00:28:46.767
- Or maybe they'll thank us
for not letting him die.

703
00:28:51.480 --> 00:28:53.857
- So we're still waiting
on your prescription.

704
00:28:53.899 --> 00:28:55.859
and the pharmacy is
a little backed up.

705
00:28:55.943 --> 00:28:58.403
But I'm glad to see
you're doing good.

706
00:28:58.445 --> 00:28:59.988
- Well.

707
00:29:00.072 --> 00:29:02.407
I'm well.

708
00:29:02.491 --> 00:29:03.909
- Glad to see you're well.

709
00:29:03.992 --> 00:29:06.870
- Can you expedite
my medication?

710
00:29:06.954 --> 00:29:09.748
- Sure. but it may still be
a little while

711
00:29:09.831 --> 00:29:14.628
before Dr. Mohan can sign off
on the discharge. so sit tight.

712
00:29:14.711 --> 00:29:17.172
- [sighs]
And do what?

713
00:29:20.550 --> 00:29:23.887
[chuckles] You just keep this
handy for occasions like this?

714
00:29:23.929 --> 00:29:26.974
- Uh. I thought that I might
not have that much to do today.

715
00:29:27.057 --> 00:29:28.892
But...

716
00:29:28.976 --> 00:29:31.436
man. I was wrong.

717
00:29:31.520 --> 00:29:34.773
[indistinct chatter]

718
00:29:37.317 --> 00:29:39.236
- Thank you.

719
00:29:43.365 --> 00:29:46.702
What brings you in today?
- A friend made me come in.

720
00:29:46.785 --> 00:29:48.704
Name's Robby.
He said I should--

721
00:29:48.787 --> 00:29:50.539
- Ah. you're Duke.

722
00:29:50.622 --> 00:29:52.124
Donnie?
- Yep?

723
00:29:52.165 --> 00:29:55.377
- Robby's VIP is here.

724
00:29:55.460 --> 00:29:57.045
[door opens]

725
00:29:57.129 --> 00:30:00.590
- Hi. I'm Donnie.
nurse practitioner.

726
00:30:00.632 --> 00:30:03.719
Robby's already put in orders
for a numbing spray

727
00:30:03.802 --> 00:30:04.970
for your nostril.

728
00:30:05.053 --> 00:30:06.805
- "Nostril"?
It's--it's my throat.

729
00:30:06.847 --> 00:30:08.724
It's not my nose.
- Okay.

730
00:30:08.807 --> 00:30:10.475
Let's get you. uh...
[device beeps]

731
00:30:10.559 --> 00:30:12.936
Set up in a room.

732
00:30:13.020 --> 00:30:14.479
- [groans]

733
00:30:14.521 --> 00:30:16.481
- That was the most
unprofessional deposition

734
00:30:16.565 --> 00:30:18.191
I've ever witnessed.

735
00:30:18.275 --> 00:30:21.695
They were nowhere near that
aggressive with Dr. Ellis.

736
00:30:21.778 --> 00:30:23.697
- Oh. okay.

737
00:30:23.780 --> 00:30:25.324
[elevator bell dings.
doors open]

738
00:30:25.407 --> 00:30:27.868
- It didn't go
as badly as you think.

739
00:30:27.951 --> 00:30:29.828
- They suggested
